/**********************************************************************
    Documentation of program contents of XDIR

    XDIR is composed of 7 program subroutines:

    XDIR     - main processing module
    YDIR     -
    ZDIR     -
    SECURE   - encryption module
    DISPLAY  - screen display module
    UTIL     - various directory utilities
    GETAPAGE - file listing routine
    CTLR     - scan files for text

    The components of each of those routines are as follows:

    XDIR
        main     - main processing routine
        action   - take requested action on files
        criteria - get the selection criteria
        dscr     - display action screen
        fcompd   - comparison routine sort files by date
        fcomps   - comparison routine sort files by size

    YDIR
        cvatt    - converts file attributes (rhsda)
        cvdate   - converts date
        dirform  -
        get1char - get a single character from console
        lis      - list a file to printer
        prin     -

    ZDIR
        bildir   - build list of directories in memory
        bilfil   - build list of files in memory
        dfnam    - display file names
        fcomp    - compare two files during sort
        fswap    - swap two files during sort
        pcomp    - compare two paths
        pswap    - swap two paths during sort

    SECURE
        cypher   - main calling routine of encryption
        secure   - security encryption routine

    DISPLAY
        boxx     - draw a box on the screen
        cvn      - convert a file name
        cvp      - convert a path name
        display  - display
        disx     -
        isval    - checks option entered is valid
        linex    - writes a line of directory info

    UTIL
        dline    - displays a line of directory info
        getpath  - extract path name
        upmod    - update directory with mode
        xcopy    - copy files
        xdump    - dump a file in hex
        xrename  - rename a file

    GETAPAGE
        bot      - display message at bottom of screen
        getxline - get a line of text from input file
        top      - display text at top of screen
        typ      - "type" a file to screen , page at a time


    CTLR
        ctlr     - main control module
        xword    - do a word comparison
        xscan    - scan a file for text strings
        getitem  - get an input item from screen
        sepname  - separate path and file name
        cline    - clear a display line
        sdir     - search a directory
        cmpext   - compare extents
        sbuff    - search a buffer for strings
        xscr     - display an input screen, get parameters

**********************************************************************/

